	<Title>
		Healthy eating: One meal at a time
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;If you&apos;re planning to improve your eating habits, good for you! But don&apos;t feel pressured to change your diet overnight. Instead, take it slow. Add a fruit or vegetable to your lunch. Choose whole-wheat pasta or brown rice for dinner. Taking it slow will help you maintain your healthier habits in the long run.&lt;/p&gt;
